{"lemma":"فِلْسَيْ","slug":"فِلْسَيْ","root":"ف.ل.س","root_slug":"ف-ل-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ل-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34506","n34508"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%90%D9%84%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a small-denomination coin, penny"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"money","tags":["colloquial","in-plural"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bankrupt, to make broke, to ruin, to render out of pennies"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cut the vines in straight line (because not every one who pruned the vines had the capacity to do so)","examples":[{"text":"الخطيب ابن حَجّاجٍ وقد اعتاد الكسّاحون عندنا ان يكون قطع القضبان من الكروم قطعا معتدلا بدون تحريف فيه ويسمونه المُفَلَّسْ وهو اغرب فى صناعتهم لانهم عندهم ليس كل الناس يقدر عليه","english":"Book on Agriculture"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"scale of a fish"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Aramaic פֵילַס (pilas) / פלס (polləs) / ܦܠܣ / פּוּלְסָא (puləsā) / ܦܘܽܠܣܴܐ (puləsā), from Ancient Greek φόλλις (phóllis), from Latin follis.\n\nDenominal verb of فِلْس (fils).\n\nBorrowed from Ancient Greek φολίς (pholís)."},"ipa":["/fils/","/fuls/","/fals/","/fal.la.sa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34506","headword_ar":"فَلْسٌ","root":"fls","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A small copper coin;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing well known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"used in buying and selling;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forty-eighth part of a dirhem:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"about half a farthing of our money:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] so in Egypt: (Ibn-Fadl-Allah, cited by Es-Suyootee in his Husn el-Mohádarah:) pl. (of pauc., S, O)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afolusN","text_ar":"اَفْلُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and (of mult., S, O)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuluwsN","text_ar":"فُلُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, O, Msb, K.) [The dim. of the former of these pls. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufayolisN","text_ar":"اُفَيْلِسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": see an ex. below, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufolisN","text_ar":"مُفْلِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". The pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuluws","text_ar":"فُلُوس"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the common term for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Money"},{"kind":"text","text":"in Egypt and some other parts in the present day.] ―         -b2-  [Hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything resembling a small coin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A counter of metal:"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b4-  and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A scale"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a fish: as Sgh says,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuluwsu Als~amaki","text_ar":"فُلُوسُ السَّمَكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what are on the back of the fish, resembling the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coins called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuluws","text_ar":"فُلُوس"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.) ―         -b5-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seal of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jizoyap","text_ar":"جِزْيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tax paid by the free non-muslim subject of a Muslim government"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (T, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which was hung upon the neck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the throat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","A","K","T","S","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n34508","headword_ar":"فَلَسٌ","root":"fls","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afolasa","text_ar":"اَفْلَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [app. signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bankruptcy"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insolvency:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state of indigence"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destitution:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lack of obtainment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"failure of finding him whom"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one seeks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaEa fiY falasK $adiydK","text_ar":"وَقَعَ فِى فَلَسٍ شَدِيدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fell into a severe state of indigence"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destitution"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Hub~ihaA falasN","text_ar":"فِى حُبِّهَا فَلَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"With her love,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the love of her, is no obtainment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~uhaA falasN","text_ar":"حُبُّهَا فَلَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a verse of El-Mo'attal El-Hudhalee, or of Aboo-Kilábeh, [in which the love thus described is afterwards termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~u mufolisN","text_ar":"حُبُّ مُفْلِسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", so that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falasN","text_ar":"فَلَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufolisN","text_ar":"مُفْلِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or the phrase is elliptical,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Her love,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the love of her, is such that nothing is obtained from it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]}]}}